               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the protagonist and of other characters like Gäbrǝʾel (fols. 15ra, 31rab, 55rb); names of the donors (in most cases only the second component); other words like sänbät “Sabbath” on fol. 15va; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I (alternating with black lines); two initial lines of subsections (miracles and commemorative notices), the first word in the incipit of subsections (hymns), i.e. sälam "salutation"; two initial lines in the incipit of Text II and of its sections; initial line in the incipit of Text III and first word of each stanza.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
